. * --- Drop zips with implausible policy intensity ---
. * Intensity > 1 means more policies than people — indicates corrupted
. * population data in the merge (e.g., 33122 Miami pop=1 vs true 1,988).
. * These zips also have wrong aweight, so drop from all regressions.
. di _n "=== Dropping zips with policy_intensity > 1 (data errors) ==="

=== Dropping zips with policy_intensity > 1 (data errors) ===

. levelsof zip if policy_intensity > 1, local(bad_zips)


. foreach z of local bad_zips {
  2.     di "  Dropping zip `z': intensity = " policy_intensity[1] " (pop corru
> pted)"
  3. }

. drop if policy_intensity > 1
(0 observations deleted)

